body:
I tried reproing this, using this little js script
```javascript

function reload(){
    loadScript("multitx.js")
}

function tx(){
    return { "from": eth.accounts[0],
        "to": "0xdddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddd",
        "value": 1,
    }
}

function batch(){
    for(var i = 0 ; i < 1000 ; i++){
        eth.sendTransaction(tx())
    }
}
```
And then starting geth with `build/bin/geth --dev console`, and calling `loadScript("multitx.js")`. Invoking the `batch()` a couple of times, and then checking `eth.getTransactionCount(eth.accounts[0])` shows that all txs have been mined. 

Please provide more info about how to reproduce this -- what type of "bulk transfer" are you using?

@holiman Thanks for your reply.
I am sending concurrent transactions with 10 or more transactions in a row. These all are erc20 token transfer. Like https://multisender.app/#/.
I solved this issue by making a tweak in this script https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/3151/how-to-make-miner-to-mine-only-when-there-are-pending-transactions.

I modified my script
```javascript

function reload(){
    loadScript("multitx.js")
}

function tx(){
    return { "from": eth.accounts[0],
        "to": "0xdddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddddd",
        "value": 1,
    }
}

function logPending(){
    console.log("pending: #" + eth.pendingTransactions.length)
}
function batch(){
    for(var i = 0 ; i < 500 ; i++){
        eth.sendTransaction(tx())
    }
    logPending()
    setTimeout(logPending, 1000)
}
```

example output:
```
> batch()
pending: #2
undefined
> pending: #0
```
Checking eth.pendingTransactions _immediately_ after submitting the transactions shows that they wind up in `pending` a short while before they are included. I am unable to otherwise reproduce the error.

Here is where clique decides not to mine a block; https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/consensus/clique/clique.go#L583 
Here is where clique is woken up for new transactions: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/miner/worker.go#L472

thanks.
In my changes, I modified the script given in this https://ethereum.stackexchange.com/questions/3151/how-to-make-miner-to-mine-only-when-there-are-pending-transactions.

**to:-**
```
var mining_threads = 1

function checkWork() {
   if (eth.pendingTransactions.length > 0) {
       if (eth.mining) return;
       console.log("== Pending transactions! Mining...");
       miner.start(mining_threads);
   } else {
       miner.stop();
       console.log("== No transactions! Mining stopped.");
   }
}

eth.filter("latest", function(err, block) { checkWork(); });
eth.filter("pending", function(err, block) { checkWork(); });

checkWork();
```
and, till now this works perfectly. I will have a look at the code and let you know.

